com.incoming.pvnsdk

Class IncomingApiServiceLocator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.incoming.pvnsdk.IncomingApiServiceLocator

  • public class IncomingApiServiceLocator
extends Object
    Provides access to the Incoming SDK API. The default Incoming SDK implementation is returned unless init(DataAccessService, VideoPlaybackEventService) is used to configure alternative implementations, such as test stubs or mocks.

    • Method Detail

      • init

        public static void init(DataAccessService dataAccessService,
                        VideoPlaybackEventService videoPlaybackEventService)
        Initialize the Incoming API entry point with alternative API implementations, such as stubs or mocks for testing. The Incoming API library will automatically initialize the API when running in an Android application, so there is no need for API consumers to call it. The Incoming API test documentation and examples show how to initialize with stub or mock API implementations to help with testing application code that uses the Incoming API.
        Parameters:
        dataAccessService - an implementation of DataAccessService
        videoPlaybackEventService - an implementation of VideoPlaybackEventService
